title: RuCo Middle School All Sports Trophy Race After Fall Sports
text:
RuCo Middle School All Sports Trophy Race After Fall Sports Published: October 21, 2015 Print 
There's a tight race for the Little Caesar's Pizza, Primetime Sports, NewsRadio WGNS Rutherford County Middle School All Sports Trophy. 
Now with fall sports complete, the Siegel girls sit atop the girl's standings with 11 points. Central Magnet is close behind with eight points and Stewarts Creek has 7. Blackman girls sit in fourth with six points. 
With only football to tally for boys standings, Blackman and Rock Springs are tied for first with seven points. Rock Springs won the regular season title but Blackman won the championship game. 
Siegel and Blackman are tied with 13 points each for the overall trophy. Rock Springs and Central Magnet are tied for third with 8 points each. 
Next up will be girls and boys basketball for middle school athletics. Related Articles
